> # To enable backgrounding for an application:
> ## (When default options are set)
> - - -
> 1. Launch the desired application.
> 1. Press and hold the Home button (the black hardware button with a white square, located at the bottom of the device).
> 1. An alert will appear, saying that backgrounding has been enabled.
> 1. Release the Home button.
> 1. After releasing the button, the alert will disappear and the application will minimize.
> 1. The application should now be running in the background.

- - -

> # To disable backgrounding for an application:
> ## (When default options are set)
> - - -
> 1. Follow the same steps as above. Note that this time the alert will say that backgrounding has been *disabled*.
